		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Apr 4th 1:04 AM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=1112573583152852124&num=9&post=1&replyto=1112591170201632527"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1112591170201632527></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=475021"><span id=Scholar>KainRostecello</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />105 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.86]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=KainRostecello&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>   Gil always seems to be a problem to whomever you meetin the game... we all need it to survive and to perform our jobs to our fullest.  This makes gil-making a competitive business, but luckily there are so many ways to make gil that the competition is spread out evenly.  This guide is by no means going to be specific as to how to make your money, although some suggestions will be made in the guide, but it should help you find your niche in the economy.<br /><br />1. Notorious Monsters<br />---------------------<br />  Most NM's drop rare items that hold some value whensold to other playersthrough the auction house, someof which hold price tags of 700k+.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. The possibility of getting rich quick.<br /> 2. The possibility of obtaining rare items you couldnt afford otherwise (like my emperor hairpin).<br /> 3. No preliinary investment required.<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. Heavy competition on the NMs of greater value (*cough* Leaping Lizzy, Valkurm Emperor) means you may not get the claim.<br /> 2. Waiting times could last from 2-3 hours on most NMs, to 24 hours or more on others.<br /> 3. Competition with bots and gilsellers on some NMs.<br /> 4. The drops are not 100% in most instances, meaning you may wind up empty-handed.<br /><br />Some Notorious Monsters and their drops:<br /> 1. Leaping Lizzy, S.Gustaberg, 700k drop, heavy competition.<br /> 2. Spiny Spipi, E.Saruta, 60-80k drop plus silk farming<br /> 3. Jaggedy-Eared Jack, 1.2Mil drop, Check my signature...<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />2. Farming<br />-----------<br /> Farming is a guaranteed source of income if your willing to put the time into it.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. You will never end the day empty-handed.<br /> 2. There are several alternative spots to camp in if there is competition. I suggest instead of having one primary farming spot, have 3 or 4 choices to cope with this competition.<br /> 3. You can actually level certain crafts farming some beastmen drops for skill-ups and better sales.<br /> 4. No preliminary investment required.<br /> 5. Um.............. Thief power!<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. Prices fluctuate with the economy.  For example, you may always make a killing selling saruta cotton in stacks, but when there are 60+ stacks of it on AH, your prone to slow sales and lower prices. See the suggestion on comment 2 under pros.<br /> 2. Some jobs just arent the best farmers (*ahem* WHM) and cannot efficiently farm even at higher levels.<br /> 3. Finishing stacks can be a pain sometimes...<br /> 4. This will NOT get you rich quick, but rather all the money from your stacks will add up over time.<br /> 5. Um...............Thief power! If you haven't levelled the THF for sub, better get busy. (TH1 helps immensly)<br /><br />Farming items:<br /> 1. Beehive chips, easy to get about anywhere, 5-8k stacks. Kill bees.<br /> 2. Silks, bad drop rate but high value (18-20k). Kill crawlers.<br /> 3. Yagudo necklaces. These can be synthesized into bronze ingots (lightning) or grass thread (wind). Also used for Norg fame...<br />---------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Mining/Logging/Harvesting<br />--------------------------<br /><br /> This can be a very viable source of income and will sell very well to craftsmen via Auction House.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. This supports crafts very well.<br /> 2. This can be easily done no matter what level you are, and will still prove to be very thrilling to higher levels (hahaha Ifrit's Cauldron)<br /> 3. Multiple areas to work and some coincide with NM pops and farming spots.<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. Requires the player to invest in tools (in stacks for efficiency).<br /> 2. The materials of highest value are incredibly rare.<br /> 3. Many materials do not stack on their own, so do gobbiebags or level a craft to support your yield (preferably the latter).<br /> 4. You CANNOT be invisible while working and sneak will wear off when you swing that pick or hatchet, so take care of aggressive mobs if you're an adventrous worker.<br /> 5. Your tools will break on random. Get stacks.<br /><br />Basic Spots to Work:<br /> 1. Zeruhn Mines, you may get lucky and get Darksteel Ore!<br /> 2. Ghelsba Outpost, there is a 5k log here, but I can't think of its name...<br /> 3. Giddeus, gooooo Fresh Mugwort, worth 15-20k each!!!<br />------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Fishing<br />---------<br /> Not my area of expertise, but here is the feedback i get from fishermen in my linkshells:<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. Some of the first things you can fish up are worth 5k a stack.<br /> 2. You get to try out the new, innovative fishing system!<br /> <br />Cons:<br /> 1. *yawn* boring in my opinion, but some people find it enjoyable.<br /> 2. It's pretty funny when you see someone throw away a rare fish because their inventory is full, so clean up!<br /> 3. Your going to break some rods and lose some bait, get over it!<br />-----------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Gardening<br />----------<br />  Gardening is a great side business to have for obtaining crystals and rare items.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. The chance of getting certain items of value, like the elemental orbs.<br /> 2. You get crystals (doesn't seem like much, but its hard to get crystals at higher levels).<br /> 3. It'll keep your moogle busy. Also doesn't detract from your time (just 2 minutes a RL day, I think you can handle that).<br /> 4. Minimal investment required per plant, adds up for large gardens though.<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. It is sloooooooow, and by slow I mean 7 RL days to a whole month!<br /> 2. It is still *somewhat* random as to what you'll yield, although yields are affected by the crystals you feed and the care you give.<br /><br /> Sorry, gardening is something you'll have to experiment with yourself, I can offer no recipes!<br />------------------------------------------<br /><br />The big cash cow, Crafting<br />--------------------------<br />  Crafting is the steadiest and most reliable source of income in the game, especially at high craftsmanship levels.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. The ability to make items that yield large sums of money.<br /> 2. The ability to make your own gear/items for yourself and friends. This means you and your friends save money.<br /> 3. Cool craft-specific equipment (the Bonecraft shades *drool*)<br /> 4. Bragging rights.<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. Some items are at the mercy of the economy. Others, like shihei and arrows, are always in demand.<br /> 2. A ridiculous amount of time and money is required to level up a craft. Goldsmithing costs millions to get to 50+...<br /> 3. Materials aren't always readily available.<br /> 4. You get bugged by members of your linkshell.<br /><br />Crafting for the Lower-Level Players:<br /> 1. Clothcraft, you can literally farm yourself to lv50.<br /> 2. Cooking, materials ar sold by many vendors all over the world to take your cooking to profitability.<br /> 3. Woodworking, like I said, arrows are always in demand, and some are relatively low level and cheap to make.<br />--------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Treasure Hunting:<br />------------------<br />  You could hunt down chests and coffers for gil and items as well.<br /><br />Pros:<br /> 1. It's fun. Break from the ordinary. Thrilling for THF too.<br /> 2. Some chests/coffers actually have good items, but these are the ones you basically have to be a Thief or a lv70+ to get the keys.<br /><br />Cons:<br /> 1. It's not fun. Finding a key AND the chest can be grueling for some crappy item that's worth only 10k.<br /> 2. If your a THF, you could pick your locks, BUT tools are expensive, lockpicking can ruin your day if you run out of tools, get weakened (for an hour+ yikes!), or *gasp* spawn a mimic.<br /> 3. If you get aggro near that chest coffer, you can kiss your sorry ass goodbye.<br />-----------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Conclusion:<br />------------<br />  I have compiled a basic run-down of every acceptable technique for making gil in the game.  No, &quot;begging&quot; and &quot;gambling&quot; are not acceptable and aren't very effective anyway.  I haven't spilled any secret NM's, farming spots, or crafting recipes, but I have given the resources needed to find your own way of making money. If i left anything out, /slap me and I'll add it.  Please enjoy the guide.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />THF52 - NIN29 - WAR30 - RNG24 - MNK15 <br />San d'Oria Rank 6 --- ZM4 Temple of Uggalepih<br />Remora Server<br />AF1 [O] - AF2 [O] - AF3 [X] - AF4 [O] - AF5 [X] - AF6 [X]<br />G1 [O] - G2 [X] - G3 [X] - G4 [X] - G5 [X]<br />{Hornetneedle} {Found it!}<br />Gambilox {Full Attack!} {Can I have it?}<br />Chandelier {Full Attack!} {Can&nbsp;&nbsp;have it?}<br />Castle Zhavl coffer *gulp* here I come...<br /><br />Jaggedy-Eared Jack ONE/99 Finally!<br />Mimics - 4<br />Weakened - 3<br />Success - 4<br /><br />LS Zeal/Evil</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Remora</td></tr></table>
