Earth:      Earth cluster  700g-1k each (not stackable)<br />Thunder  :  Lightning cluster 1.5-2.5k each (not stackable)<br /><br />Hope this helps a little!  Remember, you can also go to tahrongi canyon &amp; kill crawlers for silk threads, Pygmaoi for cotton, Dhalmels for their meat, and saplings there too.<br /><br />Alternatively, you could, as Kain suggested, camp NMs (but I usually find the amount of time to camp them I could be farming, so I rarely do- it's always a competition to see who gets to claim the mob anyway), or you could do BCNMs (give 20 Beastmen's seals to an NPC in Jeuno for a Cloudy orb and kill the NMs in the burning circle).  However, if you choose that, research what the best party setup is first.  I've done a few for fun, but never won one... because I didn't go with the optimum party.  When I do one to make money, I will make up an effective party.  In BCNM 20s, Astral rings sometimes drop- and these babys are wrth serious gil!<br /><br />Good luck with your endeavours!  <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/boozing.gif" /> </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Wondroustremor<br />Linkshell: BloodTribe (Remora)<br />http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?46812 <br />No matter how the wind howls, the mountain cannot bow to it.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Bermuda</td></tr></table>
